The Emir of Hadejia in Jigawa State, Alh. Adamu Abubakar Maje, has asked Nigeriains to intensify prayers for the peaceful conduct of the 2023 general elections. The Emir made the call on Monday when he received the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, gubernatorial candidate, Mustapha Sule Lamido, in his palace. According to the Emir, peace is the bedrock of any development of a state and a country. He advised all gubernatorial candidates and their supporters to be fervent in their prayers to God for the peaceful conduct of the polls. “We thanked almighty God for the peace we are enjoying in Jigawa State. I know people are praying hard for the peace in the state and the country, so don’t relent in your prayers especially during this crucial time.” He, however, urged people to obtain their permanent voters card in order to exercise their civic right. Earlier, the PDP gubernatorial candidate said they were at the palace to seek royal blessings and prayers from traditional rulers in the state. He also appreciated the efforts of the traditional institution in promoting peace and harmony in Jigawa State.